me, but was borne by the tragic  Lady Jane Grey  (  1537–54 ), who was unwillingly proclaimed queen in  1553 , deposed nine days later, and executed the following year. Seventy years earlier, the name had come into prominence as that of  Jane Shore , mistress of  King Edward IV  and subsequently of  Thomas Grey , 1st Marquess of Dorset, Lady Jane's grandfather. Jane Shore's tribulations in  1483  at the hands of  Richard III , Edward's brother and successor, became the subject of popular ballads and plays, which may well have increased the currency of the name in the 16th century. A 19th-century influence was its use as the name of the central character in  Charlotte Brontë's  novel Jane Eyre (  1847 ). From  1932 to 1959  it was used as the name of a cheerful and scantily clad beauty whose adventures were chronicled in a strip cartoon in the Daily Mirror. It is also borne by the American film stars  Jane Russell  (  1921–2011 ) and  Jane Fonda  (  b. 1937 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":69,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":78,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705206,"age":91,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705207,"age":105,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Johanna Trethurffe was born about 1480, in Cornwall, England, her father, John Trethurffe Esq., was 30 and her mother, Elizabeth Courtenay, was 34. She married John Tregarthen about 1499, in Devon, England. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters."},"et":{"about 1480–":"umbes 1480–Surnud","1477–1529":"1477–1529","1480–1535":"1480–1535","1480–Female":"1480–Surnud","1487–1540":"1487–1540","1495–1582":"1495–1582","1478–1503":"1478–1503","1492–1583":"1492–1583","1497–1558":"1497–1558","1451–1510":"1451–1510","1447–1510":"1447–1510","about 1492":"umbes 1492","1583":"1583","1582":"1582","1480":"1480","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1478":"1478","1510":"1510","1477":"1477","1497":"1497","about 1499":"umbes 1499","about 1497":"umbes 1497","about 1475":"umbes 1475","about 1480":"umbes 1480","1451":"1451","1495":"1495","1571":"1571","1492":"1492","1503":"1503","1447":"1447","1487":"1487","1585":"1585","1540":"1540","1529":"1529","1549":"1549","Devonshire, England":"Devon, England","Trethurffe, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","England":"England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England"},"fi":{"about 1480–":"noin 1480–Kuollut","1477–1529":"1477–1529","1480–1535":"1480–1535","1480–Female":"1480–Kuollut","1487–1540":"1487–1540","1495–1582":"1495–1582","1478–1503":"1478–1503","1492–1583":"1492–1583","1497–1558":"1497–1558","1451–1510":"1451–1510","1447–1510":"1447–1510","about 1492":"noin 1492","1583":"1583","1582":